				<p>&#8220;[..] if we are either agreeing or disagreeing, then we&#8217;re not listening, for to listen there must be an openness, an innocence, a putting away of the old ideas, so that possibly the fresh can come in.&#8221; &#8211;Joel Kramer, The Passionate Mind</p>
	            
	            				
